d as a translation of the Aramaic byname <i>Cephas</i>, given to the apostle  Simon  son of Jona, to distinguish him from another of the same name (  Simon Zelotes ). ‘When Jesus beheld him, he said, Thou art Simon the son of Jona: thou shalt be called Cephas, which is by interpretation, A stone’ (John 1:42). According to Matthew 16:17–18, Christ says more explicitly, ‘Blessed art thou, Simon Bar-jona … thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church’. The name has been in continuous use since the Middle Ages."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1702076,"age":21,"year":"1436","julianDay":2245548,"title":"The Engelbrekt Rebellion","description":"Engelbrekt Engelbrektsson, a Swedish mine owner and statesman, led a rebellion against Eric of Pomerania, King of the Kalmar Union. Sweden was upset with the Danes' interference with Swedish exports and unjust collection of taxes. The Engelbrekt Rebellion led to the deposing of Eric of Pomerania and the eventual dissolution of the Kalmar Union.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Per Stenarsson was born in 1415, in Anundsjö, Västernorrland, Sweden. He had at least 1 daughter with Karin Andersdotter Sparre. He died in 1465, in his hometown, at the age of 50."},"et":{"1415–1465":"1415–1465","1420–1470":"1420–1470","1445–Female":"1445–Surnud","1415":"1415","abt 1445":"umbes 1445","1436":"1436","1445":"1445","1465":"1465","1420":"1420","1470":"1470","Sweden":"Rootsi","Anundsjö, Västernorrland, Sweden":"Anundsjö, Västernorrland, Rootsi"},"fi":{"1415–1465":"1415–1465","1420–1470":"1420–1470","1445–Female":"1445–Kuollut","1415":"1415","abt 1445":"noin 1445","1436":"1436","1445":"1445","1465":"1465","1420":"1420","1470":"1470","Sweden":"Ruotsi","Anundsjö, Västernorrland, Sweden":"Anundsjö, Västernorrland, Ruotsi"},"fr":{"1415–1465":"1415–1465","1420–1470":"1420–1470","1445–Female":"1445–Décédée","1415":"1415","abt 1445":"environ 1445","1436":"1436","1445":"1445","1465":"1465","1420":"1420","1470":"1470","Sweden":"Suède","Anun